Type: Package
Package: optimTFE
Title: Conservation recovery planning via optimization algorithm
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Christina R Leopold, Devin R Leopold
Maintainer: Christina R Leopold <cleopold@usgs.gov>
Description: OptimTFE is a spatial decision-support tool designed to help conservation
practitioners identify priority recovery areas for species/taxonomic groups based on
known location data, habitat suitability values, and other relevant data inputs.
The tool can be used for any dataset that includes suitability values for each species
and a target number of priority recovery areas for each.
